<p>I am using angular-facebook-utils to integrate Facebook authentication on a site I'm building.  The login works fine globally but the logout only works from the homepage.  If I navigate to a subpage and try to logout it makes it into the function but FB.logout is never called.  Also, if I navigate to a subpage and back home it doesn't get called.</p>  <pre><code>FacebookUser.prototype.logout = function() {             console.log('component logout called');             var _self = this;             console.log(_self, FB, FB.logout.toString());             console.log(FB);             FB.logout(function(response) {                 console.log('***',response);                 if (response) {                     _self.loggedIn = false;                     $rootScope.$broadcast("fbLogoutSuccess");                 } else {                     $rootScope.$broadcast("fbLogoutFailure");                     FB.Auth.setAuthResponse(null, 'unknown');                 }             });         }; </code></pre>